2002-12-23  Jaka Mocnik  <jaka@gnu.org>

	* configure.in: bumped version to 1.99.97; tagged as GGV_1_99_97.
	* bonobo/ggv-sidebar.c: fixed a typo causing a mis-cast.
	* src/ggv-window.c: applied a patch from chris at gnome-de dot org
	that fixes the copyright string.

2002-12-17  Rajkumar Sivasamy  <rajkumar.siva@wipro.com>

	* ggv-prefs-ui.c: Set mnemonics to controls in preferences dialog.
	Fixes bug #101434

2002-12-13  Jaka Mocnik  <jaka@gnu.org>

	* applied patches that add startup notification and priority text
	to icons.

2002-11-29  Yanko Kaneti <yaneti@declera.com>

	* src/ggv-window.c (ggv_window_load): add a missing prameter to the
	g_locale_to_utf8 call from the previous patch. Fixes tinderbox.

2002-11-28  Jaka Mocnik  <jaka@gnu.org>

	* src/ggv-window.c (ggv_window_load): applied a patch from Hidetoshi
	Tajima to convert title to utf-8 before setting it.

2002-11-27  Jaka Mocnik  <jaka@gnu.org>

	* src/gtkgs.c (gtk_gs_set_page_size): respect bounding box if
	requested.
	* bonobo/ggv-control.c (ggv_control_create_ui): set fit width pixbuf
	to popup ui component. use smaller pixbufs for menu and popup menu
	than for toolbar.
	* bonobo/ggv-postscript-view-ui.xml: removed pixtype="none".

2002-11-22  Jaka Mocnik  <jaka@gnu.org>

	* src/gtkgs.c (gtk_gs_goto_page): a fix for bug #85004.
	* src/ggv-prefs-ui.c (ggv_prefs_dialog_new): renamed right-hans side
	panel option.
	* src/ggvutils.c: removed zoom factors larger than 6.0 and smaller
	than 1.0/6.0.

2002-11-19  Jaka Mocnik  <jaka@gnu.org>

	* bonobo/ggv-postscript-view-ui-xml: removed "Override*" commands
	and menu items. added "OrientationDocument" and "PaperSizeDoc"
	commands and menu items. this allows for single-click setting of
	orientation and size.
	* bonobo/ggv-postscript-view.c: support the above changes.
	optimized menu syncing.
	* src/gtkgs.[ch]: constification of parameters.
	* src/gtkgs.c, src/ps.c: better handling of page and document
	orientations.

2002-11-15  Jaka Mocnik  <jaka@gnu.org>

	* bonobo/ggv-postscript-view.c (ggv_postscript_view_create_ui): freeze
	UI component _before_ merging UI. this enables us to put sidebar
	on the right when opening a window.
	* src/ggv-prefs-ui.c (ggv_prefs_dialog_new): fixed placement of
	orientation choice menu.

2002-11-13  Dmitry G. Mastrukov  <dmitry@taurussoft.org>

	* configure.in: Added Belarusian to ALL_LINGUAS.

2002-11-10  Jaka Mocnik  <jaka@gnu.org>

        * configure.in: moved version to 1.99.96. tagged as GGV_1_99_96.

2002-11-09  Jaka Mocnik  <jaka@gnu.org>

	* src/ggv-ui.xml: moved Layout submenu from Edit to View menu.
	fixes #97843.
	* bonobo/ggv-postscript-view-ui.xml: fixed accelerators for
	navigation. fixes #97842.
	* src/gtkgs.c (gtk_gs_goto_page): applied patch from satyajit that
	fixes occasional erroneous refreshes of non-structured docs. fixes
	#97828.
	* bonobo/ggv-sidebar.c (ggv_sidebar_construct): change coordinate
	widget to GtkEntry instead of GtkLabel in order to prevent resizing
	when text grows. make it horizontally as small as possible! fixes
	#97711.

2002-11-06  Jaka Mocnik  <jaka@gnu.org>

	* acconfig.h: remove. changes from 2002-11-04 have rendered it
	unnecessary.

2002-11-05  Jaka Mocnik  <jaka@gnu.org>

	* src/gtkgs.[ch], src/gsdefaults.[ch], src/ggv-prefs-ui.c,
	bonobo/ggv-postscript-view.c, ggv.schemas: from now on, we no
	longer make a DSC file from PDF and use it to navigate through PDF,
	but instead we convert every PDF to PS and show it. benefits?
	enables printing and saving of PDF files and solves some issues
	with deducing orientation and page size from PDFs. cost? a bit
	slower, especially for large PDFs.

2002-11-04  Jaka Mocnik  <jaka@gnu.org>

	* acconfig.h: removed, so that newer autoconfs don't spit warnings
	about deprecation at us.
	* configure.in: added 3rd arg to AC_DEFINE*() in order to get nice
	comments in config.h.
	* bonobo/main.c (ggv_postscript_viewer_factory): removed signal
	handlers as they caused ggv to hang when rapidly starting/stopping
	interpreter.
	* bonobo/ggv-control.c: sync auto-fit items with defaults on startup
	and set their sensitivity according to the status of the loaded
	document.

2002-11-03  Jaka Mocnik  <jaka@gnu.org>

	* bonobo/ggv-control.c: handle selection of auto-fit mode.
	(ggv_control_construct): unref the GtkGS we get from GgvPostScriptView.
	* bonobo/ggv-control-ui.xml: added a menu for selection of auto-fit
	mode.
	* src/ggv-prefs-ui.[ch]: implemented a choice menu for setting the
	default zoom mode for GtkGS widgets!
	* src/ggvutils.[ch]: removed some obsolete func prototypes.
	added ggv_auto_fit_modes.
	* src/gsdefaults.[ch]: handle default zoom mode.
	* src/gtkgs.[ch]: added GtkGSZoomMode enum and zoom_mode member to
	GtkGS. implemented auto-fit functionality.

2002-10-30  Jaka Mocnik  <jaka@gnu.org>

	* configure.in: added G*_DISABLE_DEPRECATED to GGV_CFLAGS.
	* */*.[ch]: elimination of deprecated code.
	* ggv.schemas: added pageflip and scrollstep keys.
	* src/gsdefaults.c: added scroll_step setting: tells what percentage
	of viewable area size will be used for scrolling.
	* src/ggv-prefs.[ch], src/ggv-prefs-ui.[ch]: implemented configuration
	for scroll step.
	* bonobo/ggv-postscript-view.c (ggv_postscript_view_construct):
	read gconf setting for "pageflip": if true, pages will be flipped
	automatically when scrolled to the edge of document.
	* bonobo/ggv-control.c (zoomable_set_zoom_level_cb): only modify the
	adjustment value if it is different from the zoom level being set.
	* src/gtkgs.c (gtk_gs_get_postscript): copy whole non-structured doc.
	* bonobo/ggv-control-ui.xml: added missing tooltips.

2002-10-29  Christian Neumair  <chris@gnome-de.org>

	* src/ggv-prefs-ui.c: Make button sequence HIG compliant.

2002-10-26  Jaka Mocnik  <jaka@gnu.org>

	* src/ggv-window.c (verb_FileClose): if the document being closed is
	the last one, just tell the PostScriptView component to unload the
	document and leave the window open. fixes #96792.
	(control_property_changed_handler): only display status message if
	status is non-empty.
	* idl/Ggv.idl: added close() method.
	* bonobo/ggv-postscript-view.c (impl_GNOME_GGV_PostScriptView_close):
	implemented the close() method.

